      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAN'T TOUCH ME (8) finished well back at this track last time when a 5.5 lengths seventh (24.19) but scored three back at this track (23.66). Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can make amends. BARGARA KILLIAN (1) took the sit on the lead from a low draw but levelled up and led around the bend to score (23.72) at this track in a Mix 5 over 407m. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. BAHAMA BLUE (6) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 23.77 beating Jackpot Junior. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. One of the key runners again. SIRIUS BILLY (3) is a course and distance winner who is right in the equation.",
